<figureCitation id="80D941B65752FF853E7DFA1F04BDF980" box="[831,904,1530,1554]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[1134,1167,1317,1339]" captionTargetBox="[211,1058,241,1389]" captionTargetId="figure-328@14.[189,1096,219,1389]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 6. Chimerocoris luridus sp.n. ♂: A: dorsal; B: ventral; C: lateral. Scale bars = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4360237" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4360237/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">Figs. 6</figureCitation>
A– C, 
<figureCitation id="80D941B65752FF853E8FFA1F04EFF980" box="[973,986,1530,1554]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[151,184,1114,1136]" captionTargetBox="[151,1398,216,1093]" captionTargetId="figure-468@15.[151,1398,216,1093]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Chimerocoris luridus sp.n. ♂: Male terminalia: A– D: dorsal; B–E: posterior; C–F: ventral. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4360243" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4360243/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">7</figureCitation>
A– F, 
<figureCitation id="80D941B65752FF853958FA1F0302F980" box="[1050,1079,1530,1554]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="28.[189,222,1311,1333]" captionTargetBox="[209,1417,245,1273]" captionTargetId="figure-325@28.[189,1436,219,1296]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Fig. 17. Map of geographical distribution. — Colors: yellow – Chimerocoris luridus sp.n.; purple – Hypanthracos meridionalis; red – Liscocephala fumosa sp.n.; green – Ogmocoris Mayr, 1864; blue – Triunfus gen. n." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4360283" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4360283/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">17</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="80D941B65752FF853900FA1F0368F980" box="[1090,1117,1530,1554]" captionStart="←" captionStartId="30.[189,212,1914,1935]" captionTargetBox="[167,1382,237,2080]" captionTargetId="figure-39@31.[150,1397,219,2094]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="← Fig. 18. Representation and comparison of head and thoracic characters. A–C: head, dorsal view; D–E: head and prothorax, lateral view (antennomeres not showing due to edition of photo); F: schematic drawing showing the antennomeres; G–S: external scent efferent system; G–N: meso- and metapleura, ventral view; G: schematic drawing showing the parts of eses; O–S: SEM images of characters of eses of mestasternal glands. — (A, Fi, H): Hypanthracos meridionalis; (B, N): Mecocephala magna; (C): Paramecocephala foveata; (D, M): Tibraca limbativentris; (E, S): Hypatropis inermis; (Fii, I): Chimerocoris luridus; (Fiii, J): Ogmocoris hypomelas; (Fiv, K): Liscocephala fumosa; (Fv, L): Triunfus carvalhoi; (O): Glyphepomis adroguensis; (P): Paramecocephala fusca; (Q): Pedinonotus catarinensis; (R): Glyphepomis setigera; Scale bars: A–E, H–N = 0.5 mm; O–S = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4360291" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4360291/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">18</figureCitation>
Fii, I, 
<figureCitation id="80D941B65752FF8539E7FA1F03F5F980" box="[1189,1216,1530,1554]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="32.[189,222,1983,2005]" captionTargetBox="[163,1381,242,1375]" captionTargetId="figure-352@33.[151,1398,220,1397]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Fig. 19. Comparative figure of Chimerocoris, Paramecocephala and Tibraca. A–C: habitus dorsal (antennomeres and legs not showing due to edition of photo); D–E: head and pronotum; F–G: habitus ventral; H–I: habitus lateral; J–R: male terminalia: J, M, P: dorsal view; K, N, Q: posterior view; L, O, R: ventral view. — (A, D, F, H, J–L): Chimerocoris luridus; (B, I, M–O): Paramecocephala fusca; (C, E, G, P–R): Tibraca exigua. Scale bars:A– C, F– I = 2.0 mm; D–E = 0.5 mm; J–R = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4360301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4360301/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">19</figureCitation>
A, D, F, H, J – L
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="50F80EB85752FF853E7DF9DF0319F8A0" pageId="14" pageNumber="335" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="185D5D335752FF853E7DF9DF0319F8A0" blockId="14.[831,1437,1594,1842]" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis id="2A9681215752FF853E7DF9DF0481F9C0" bold="true" box="[831,948,1594,1618]" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Each antennomere 3 cylindrical, shorter than 5 and antennomeres 4 conical, convex dorsally. Bucculae truncate, reaching base of head. Labium long, surpassing the middle of abdominal sternite 6. Anterolateral margins of pronotum not reflexed. Basal angles of scutellum with foveae subequal to the diameter of a compound eye. Seg-ment X ogival, with a transverse carina and 1 + 1 thorn-like processes at base.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="50F80EB85752FF843E02F8BF04DEFAE4" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="336" pageId="14" pageNumber="335" type="description">
<paragraph id="185D5D335752FF843E02F8BF0336FAA6" blockId="14.[831,1437,1881,2098]" lastBlockId="15.[794,1399,1210,1332]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="336" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis id="2A9681215752FF853E02F8BF035BF8E3" bold="true" box="[832,1134,1882,1906]" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">
Description. 
<emphasis id="2A9681215752FF853E8DF8BF035BF8E3" bold="true" box="[975,1134,1882,1905]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">Measurements</emphasis>
</emphasis>
: Table 4. 
<emphasis id="2A9681215752FF853995F8BC026FF8E3" bold="true" box="[1239,1370,1881,1905]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">Colouration</emphasis>
: General colour yellowish-brown dorsally and ventrally, densely punctate (
<figureCitation id="80D941B65752FF853957F87F03BFF820" box="[1045,1162,1946,1970]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[1134,1167,1317,1339]" captionTargetBox="[211,1058,241,1389]" captionTargetId="figure-328@14.[189,1096,219,1389]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 6. Chimerocoris luridus sp.n. ♂: A: dorsal; B: ventral; C: lateral. Scale bars = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4360237" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4360237/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">Fig. 6A, B</figureCitation>
). Head with calloused, yellow longitudinal stripes on clypeus medially; anten-nomeres uniformly brownish (
<figureCitation id="80D941B65752FF8539DBF83F03C5F860" box="[1177,1264,2010,2034]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[1134,1167,1317,1339]" captionTargetBox="[211,1058,241,1389]" captionTargetId="figure-328@14.[189,1096,219,1389]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 6. Chimerocoris luridus sp.n. ♂: A: dorsal; B: ventral; C: lateral. Scale bars = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4360237" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4360237/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
); antenniferous tubercles and maxillary plates brown. Outline of ante-rolateral margins of pronotum yellowish. Femora, tibiae and tarsi yellowish (
<figureCitation id="80D941B65753FF843C3DFB5F06D5FB40" box="[383,480,1210,1234]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[1134,1167,1317,1339]" captionTargetBox="[211,1058,241,1389]" captionTargetId="figure-328@14.[189,1096,219,1389]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 6. Chimerocoris luridus sp.n. ♂: A: dorsal; B: ventral; C: lateral. Scale bars = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4360237" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4360237/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="336">Figs. 6A</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="80D941B65753FF843CA9FB5F0528FB40" box="[491,541,1210,1234]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="32.[189,222,1983,2005]" captionTargetId="figure-352@33.[151,1398,220,1397]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Fig. 19. Comparative figure of Chimerocoris, Paramecocephala and Tibraca. A–C: habitus dorsal (antennomeres and legs not showing due to edition of photo); D–E: head and pronotum; F–G: habitus ventral; H–I: habitus lateral; J–R: male terminalia: J, M, P: dorsal view; K, N, Q: posterior view; L, O, R: ventral view. — (A, D, F, H, J–L): Chimerocoris luridus; (B, I, M–O): Paramecocephala fusca; (C, E, G, P–R): Tibraca exigua. Scale bars:A– C, F– I = 2.0 mm; D–E = 0.5 mm; J–R = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4360301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4360301/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="336">19D</figureCitation>
). Connexivum yel-low, each connexivum with blotchy spot brown in the posterolateral angles (
<figureCitation id="80D941B65753FF843CD1FB1F06DFFA80" box="[403,490,1274,1298]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[1134,1167,1317,1339]" captionTargetBox="[211,1058,241,1389]" captionTargetId="figure-328@14.[189,1096,219,1389]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 6. Chimerocoris luridus sp.n. ♂: A: dorsal; B: ventral; C: lateral. Scale bars = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4360237" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4360237/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="336">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Sternites brown with darkened punctures; antero- and posterolateral angles of sternites dark brown (
<figureCitation id="80D941B65753FF843CE1FADF06CFFAC0" box="[419,506,1338,1362]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[1134,1167,1317,1339]" captionTargetBox="[211,1058,241,1389]" captionTargetId="figure-328@14.[189,1096,219,1389]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 6. Chimerocoris luridus sp.n. ♂: A: dorsal; B: ventral; C: lateral. Scale bars = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4360237" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4360237/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="336">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
). Sternites 3 – 7 yellow sublaterally, with concolourous trichobothria and punc-tures (
<figureCitation id="80D941B65753FF843D98FA9F061AFA00" box="[218,303,1402,1426]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[1134,1167,1317,1339]" captionTargetBox="[211,1058,241,1389]" captionTargetId="figure-328@14.[189,1096,219,1389]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 6. Chimerocoris luridus sp.n. ♂: A: dorsal; B: ventral; C: lateral. Scale bars = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4360237" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4360237/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="336">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
). Spiracles dark brown. 
<emphasis id="2A9681215753FF843F76FA9C055AFA03" bold="true" box="[564,623,1401,1425]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="336">Head</emphasis>
: Anteocular processes present. Proportions of antennomeres: 1 &lt;2&gt; 3 &lt;4 &lt;5. Posterior margins of bucculae reaching base of head. Labiomere 2 shorter than labiomeres 3 and 4 com-bined (
<figureCitation id="80D941B65753FF843DA7FA1F060BF980" box="[229,318,1530,1554]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[1134,1167,1317,1339]" captionTargetBox="[211,1058,241,1389]" captionTargetId="figure-328@14.[189,1096,219,1389]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 6. Chimerocoris luridus sp.n. ♂: A: dorsal; B: ventral; C: lateral. Scale bars = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4360237" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4360237/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="336">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="2A9681215753FF843C16FA1C0693F983" bold="true" box="[340,422,1529,1553]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="336">Thorax</emphasis>
: Anterior angles of pronotum not produced; anterolateral margins of pronotum straight and smooth; humeral angles not produced (
<figureCitation id="80D941B65753FF843FC2F9DF05DDF9C0" box="[640,744,1594,1618]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="32.[189,222,1983,2005]" captionTargetId="figure-352@33.[151,1398,220,1397]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Fig. 19. Comparative figure of Chimerocoris, Paramecocephala and Tibraca. A–C: habitus dorsal (antennomeres and legs not showing due to edition of photo); D–E: head and pronotum; F–G: habitus ventral; H–I: habitus lateral; J–R: male terminalia: J, M, P: dorsal view; K, N, Q: posterior view; L, O, R: ventral view. — (A, D, F, H, J–L): Chimerocoris luridus; (B, I, M–O): Paramecocephala fusca; (C, E, G, P–R): Tibraca exigua. Scale bars:A– C, F– I = 2.0 mm; D–E = 0.5 mm; J–R = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4360301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4360301/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="336">Fig. 19D</figureCitation>
). Periostiolar depressions of ESES present; each peritreme extending about ⅔ of the distance to lateral margin of evaporatorium; gyrification of evaporatorium with high wrinkles; anterolateral margin of each evaporatorium rounded; outer margin of each metapleural evapora-torium concave (
<figureCitation id="80D941B65753FF843C1EF91F0680F880" box="[348,437,1786,1810]" captionStart="←" captionStartId="30.[189,212,1914,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-39@31.[150,1397,219,2094]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="← Fig. 18. Representation and comparison of head and thoracic characters. A–C: head, dorsal view; D–E: head and prothorax, lateral view (antennomeres not showing due to edition of photo); F: schematic drawing showing the antennomeres; G–S: external scent efferent system; G–N: meso- and metapleura, ventral view; G: schematic drawing showing the parts of eses; O–S: SEM images of characters of eses of mestasternal glands. — (A, Fi, H): Hypanthracos meridionalis; (B, N): Mecocephala magna; (C): Paramecocephala foveata; (D, M): Tibraca limbativentris; (E, S): Hypatropis inermis; (Fii, I): Chimerocoris luridus; (Fiii, J): Ogmocoris hypomelas; (Fiv, K): Liscocephala fumosa; (Fv, L): Triunfus carvalhoi; (O): Glyphepomis adroguensis; (P): Paramecocephala fusca; (Q): Pedinonotus catarinensis; (R): Glyphepomis setigera; Scale bars: A–E, H–N = 0.5 mm; O–S = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4360291" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4360291/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="336">
Fig. 
<date id="6C5C7BF35753FF843CCCF91F0680F880" box="[398,437,1786,1810]" pageId="15" pageNumber="336" value="2018-01">18I</date>
</figureCitation>
). Corium surpassing apices of abdominal tergite 5. Membrane with veins linear. Hemelytra not surpassing apex of abdomen (
<figureCitation id="80D941B65753FF843FD3F8DF05DDF8C0" box="[657,744,1850,1874]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[1134,1167,1317,1339]" captionTargetBox="[211,1058,241,1389]" captionTargetId="figure-328@14.[189,1096,219,1389]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 6. Chimerocoris luridus sp.n. ♂: A: dorsal; B: ventral; C: lateral. Scale bars = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4360237" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4360237/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="336">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="2A9681215753FF843DD5F8BC0634F8E3" bold="true" box="[151,257,1881,1905]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="336">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Posterolateral angles of each connexivum not produced. 
<emphasis id="2A9681215753FF843C4FF89C06F1F803" bold="true" box="[269,452,1913,1937]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="336">Male terminalia</emphasis>
: Pygophore subrectangular (
<figureCitation id="80D941B65753FF843DE2F87F061FF823" box="[160,298,1946,1970]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[151,184,1114,1136]" captionTargetBox="[151,1398,216,1093]" captionTargetId="figure-468@15.[151,1398,216,1093]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Chimerocoris luridus sp.n. ♂: Male terminalia: A– D: dorsal; B–E: posterior; C–F: ventral. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4360243" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4360243/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="336">Figs. 7A – F</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="80D941B65753FF843C75F87F06B0F823" box="[311,389,1946,1970]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="32.[189,222,1983,2005]" captionTargetId="figure-352@33.[151,1398,220,1397]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Fig. 19. Comparative figure of Chimerocoris, Paramecocephala and Tibraca. A–C: habitus dorsal (antennomeres and legs not showing due to edition of photo); D–E: head and pronotum; F–G: habitus ventral; H–I: habitus lateral; J–R: male terminalia: J, M, P: dorsal view; K, N, Q: posterior view; L, O, R: ventral view. — (A, D, F, H, J–L): Chimerocoris luridus; (B, I, M–O): Paramecocephala fusca; (C, E, G, P–R): Tibraca exigua. Scale bars:A– C, F– I = 2.0 mm; D–E = 0.5 mm; J–R = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4360301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4360301/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="336">19J – L</figureCitation>
