<figureCitation id="80D941B65753FF843E60FB3F0443FB61" box="[802,886,1242,1267]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[151,184,1114,1136]" captionTargetBox="[151,1398,216,1093]" captionTargetId="figure-468@15.[151,1398,216,1093]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Chimerocoris luridus sp.n. ♂: Male terminalia: A– D: dorsal; B–E: posterior; C–F: ventral. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4360243" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4360243/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="336">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
). Inferior layer of ventral rim with 1 + 1 pro-cesses (
<figureCitation id="80D941B65753FF843E29FB1E0488FA81" box="[875,957,1275,1299]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[151,184,1114,1136]" captionTargetBox="[151,1398,216,1093]" captionTargetId="figure-468@15.[151,1398,216,1093]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Chimerocoris luridus sp.n. ♂: Male terminalia: A– D: dorsal; B–E: posterior; C–F: ventral. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4360243" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4360243/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="336">Fig. 7F</figureCitation>
). Segment X ogival. Crown of parameres trapezoidal (
<figureCitation id="80D941B65753FF843EE2FAF904C3FAA6" box="[928,1014,1308,1332]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[151,184,1114,1136]" captionTargetBox="[151,1398,216,1093]" captionTargetId="figure-468@15.[151,1398,216,1093]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Chimerocoris luridus sp.n. ♂: Male terminalia: A– D: dorsal; B–E: posterior; C–F: ventral. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4360243" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4360243/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="336">Fig. 7D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
